ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Since March 1, 2020, have you needed to postpone any medical procedures?
In the past month, have you missed any scheduled appointments with any healthcare providers?
Notes: 0 = No; 1 = Yes; 97 = Do not know; 98 = Refused

ElementDescription: What is the MAIN reason you missed appointments with any healthcare provider in the past month?
Notes: 1 = Clinic cancelled appointment; 2 = Clinic closed; 3 = Had symptoms of COVID-19; 4 = Cancelled appointment, avoid others; 5 = Cancelled appointment, avoid healthcare; 6 = Felt ok, or good enough; 7 = Did not have money or insurance; 8 = Didn't want to take public trans; 9 = Forgot or missed appt; 10 = Felt disrespected by staff; 11 = Were drinking or taking drugs; 12 = Other reason; 88 = N/A; 97 = Do not know; 98 = Refused to answer

ElementDescription: Specify other reason for missing your appointments
In the past month, have you missed taking any medications?
Notes: 0 = No; 1 = Yes; 97 = Do not know; 98 = Refused

ElementDescription: What is the MAIN reason you missed taking medications in the past month?
Notes: 1 = Pharmacy closed; 2 = Couldn't go to pharmacy, shutdown; 3 = Couldn't go to pharmacy, avoid others; 4 = Felt food, didn't need medications; 5 = Doctor advised delayed treatment; 6 = Worried about side effects; 7 = Did not have money or insurance; 8 = Didn't want to take public transportation; 9 = Were drinking or using drugs; 10 = Forgot to take medications; 11 = Other reason; 88 = N/A; 97 = Do not know; 98 = Refused to answer

ElementDescription: Specify other reason for missing meds

Notes: 0=Below 50 copies/mL (undetectable or suppressed); 1=50 copies/mL or more (detectable or raised); 2=Don''t know
